  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, Department of Energy contract obligations total $45.7B across 3,729 awards with an average award size of $12.3M. Obligations are down 5.8% year over year. Facilities Support Services accounts for the largest share of obligations at $23.2B, followed by several research and development categories that together represent a substantial portion of obligations, including $6.9B for Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences and $3.4B for Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology). Remediation Services and Other chemical and technical categories also appear among the top NAICS entries with $2.9B and $2.8B respectively. The top vendor list is concentrated among national laboratory contractors and large systems integrators, led by TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC at $5.1B and NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC at $4.5B, with multiple vendors in the $1.6B–$3.3B range. FY26 totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has DOE contract spending trended year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations are down 5.8% year over year. Fiscal totals show growth from FY21’s $37.7B to FY25’s $48.5B, with FY26 at $45.7B to date. The FY26-to-date total is a partial fiscal-year figure. Yearly figures provide a multi‑year context for the current decline."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which contract categories and vendors dominate FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "Facilities Support Services dominates with $23.2B in obligations, while major R&D categories total $6.9B and $3.4B in their respective entries. The top vendors are led by TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC at $5.1B and NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC at $4.5B, followed by several contractors with multi‑billion dollar obligations. Combined category and vendor concentrations indicate a focus on lab operations, R&D, remediation, and associated professional services."
      }
    ]
  },
  "faq": [
    {
      "q": "How much does Department of Energy spend on contracts?",
      "a": "The Department of Energy spends $45.7B on contracts FY2026 to date. That total covers 3,729 awards with an average award size of $12.3M and represents a year‑over‑year change of down 5.8%. FY26 totals are partial (fiscal year to date)."
    },
    {
      "q": "What does Energy buy?",
      "a": "Energy buys a large volume of Facilities Support Services and research and development work. Facilities Support Services accounts for $23.2B, Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences accounts for $6.9B, and Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology) accounts for $3.4B, alongside remediation, chemical manufacturing, and other technical services."
    },
    {
      "q": "Who are Energy's largest contractors?",
      "a": "Energy's largest contractors are concentrated among national laboratory and site-management firms. TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC leads with $5.1B, followed by NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC at $4.5B, SAVANNAH RIVER NUCLEAR SOLUTIONS LLC at $3.3B, LAWRENCE LIVERMORE NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC at $3.3B, and CONSOLIDATED NUCLEAR SECURITY, LLC at $2.9B, with additional top vendors ranging down to PANTEXAS DETERRENCE, LLC at $1.6B."
    }
